class="block block-rank-table"><h2 id=alabama-business-filing-fees>Alabama Business Filing Fees:</h2><div
class="table-wrapper"><div
class="table-responsive"><table
class="table"><tbody><tr><th><p>Filing Type</p></th><th><p>Fee</p></th></tr><tr><td><p>Name Reservation</p></td><td><p>$25.00 (+ $3.00 for online applications)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Certificate of Existence</p></td><td><p>$25.00 (+ $3.00 for online applications)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Certificate of Formation (all domestic entities)</p></td><td><p>$200.00</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Filings for Domestic For-Profit Corporation</p></td><td><p>$200.00</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>General Partnership</p></td><td><p>$200.00</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="section-faq"><div
class="container"><h2 id=fAQs class="section-heading">FAQs:</h2><div
class="row"><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-is-required-to-open-a-business-in-alabama class="question">What is required to open a business in Alabama?</h3><div
class="answer"><ul><li>Name Reservation Request form.</li><li>Employer identification number.</li><li>Business registration.</li><li>All necessary permits and licenses.</li><li>Business tax registration.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-to-start-a-business-in-alabama class="question">How much does it cost to start a business in Alabama?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Alabama's <a
href="#alabama-business-filing-fees">business filing fees</a> can range from $25.00 to $200.00 per reservation.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=do-i-need-a-business-license-to-be-self-employed-in-alabama class="question">Do I need a business license to be self employed in Alabama?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>If you choose to operate your business as a sole proprietorship, you do not need a business license. However, you do need a business privilege license for every county in Alabama where you conduct business. You can apply for this license from the county probate court.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=do-you-need-a-business-license-to-sell-in-alabama class="question">Do you need a business license to sell in Alabama?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>All persons or businesses that engage in trade, commerce, or a profession for gain or profit must pay a license fee. You may also need a license from the city or county in which you will be operating.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-start-a-business-in-alabama-online class="question">How do I start a business in Alabama online?</h3><div
class="answer"><ol><li><a
href="#review-alabama-formation-options">Choose a formation option</a>.</li><li><a
href="#name-your-business">Decide on a business name</a>.</li><li><a
href="#get-an-employer-identification-number">Get your Employer Identification Number</a>.</li><li><a
href="#register-your-business-in-alabama">Register your business</a>.</li><li><a
href="#obtain-necessary-permits-and-licenses">Apply for your licenses and permits</a>.</li><li><a
href="#register-your-business-for-taxes">Register for taxes</a>.</li></ol></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=should-i-use-the-alabama-secretary-of-state-for-my-business-needs class="question">Should I use the Alabama Secretary of State for my business needs?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Yes, you will be registering your business and reserving your business name on the Secretary of State website. As a business owner in Alabama, you will also find other useful tools, materials, information, and tips on the SOS website.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-start-a-business-in-alabama-from-home class="question">How do I start a business in Alabama from home?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Follow our <a
href="#how-to-start-a-business-in-alabama">step-by-step guide</a> to form and register your Alabama business from the comfort of your own home.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=can-i-do-an-alabama-secretary-of-state-business-registration class="question">Can I do an Alabama Secretary of State business registration?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Yes, you can register your business with the Alabama Secretary of State.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-register-a-business-in-alabama class="question">How do I register a business in Alabama?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>You can register either by mail by sending your completed application form, Name Reservation Certificate, and application fee to the Office of the Judge of Probate in the county where your business's registered office is located, or by going to the <a
href="https://www.alabamainteractive.org/sos/introduction_input.action">Alabama Secretary of State's online portal</a> and completing the online application.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=can-i-get-an-alabama-business-license-online class="question">Can I get an Alabama business license online?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>When starting a business in Alabama, you will need a privilege license from the state, issued by the Probate Judge or License Commissioner in the county where your business is located. However, you may also need different types of business privilege licenses, depending on your business's services and products.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=where-can-i-find-an-alabama-business-license-application class="question">Where can I find an Alabama business license application?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>You can find the appropriate form on <a
href="https://www.sos.alabama.gov/business-entities/business-downloads">Alabama's SOS website</a>.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-start-an-llc-in-alabama class="question">How do I start an LLC in Alabama?</h3><div
class="answer"><ul><li>Reserve your business name.</li><li>Hire a registered agent.</li><li>File Certificate of Formation.</li><li>Create an operating procedure.</li><li>Apply for your employer identification number.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=where-can-i-do-an-online-name-reservation-in-alabama class="question">Where can I do an online name reservation in Alabama?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>In Alabama, you can reserve your chosen business name on the <a
href="https://www.alabamainteractive.org/sos/welcome.action">SOS Online Services portal</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div> <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is required to open a business in Alabama?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<ul>\n<li>Name Reservation Request form.<\/li>\n<li>Employer identification number.<\/li>\n<li>Business registration.<\/li>\n<li>All necessary permits and licenses.<\/li>\n<li>Business tax registration.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does it cost to start a business in Alabama?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>Alabama's <a href=\"#alabama-business-filing-fees\">business filing fees<\/a> can range from $25.00 to $200.00 per reservation.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need a business license to be self employed in Alabama?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>If you choose to operate your business as a sole proprietorship, you do not need a business license. However, you do need a business privilege license for every county in Alabama where you conduct business. You can apply for this license from the county probate court.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you need a business license to sell in Alabama?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>All persons or businesses that engage in trade, commerce, or a profession for gain or profit must pay a license fee. You may also need a license from the city or county in which you will be operating.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I start a business in Alabama online?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#review-alabama-formation-options\">Choose a formation option<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#name-your-business\">Decide on a business name<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#get-an-employer-identification-number\">Get your Employer Identification Number<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#re